  "prompt": "What are G4 nations?",
  "response": "The G4 nations, also known as the Group of Four, are a coalition of four countries that support each other's bids for permanent seats on the United Nations Security Council. These countries are:\n\n1. Brazil\n2. Germany\n3. India\n4. Japan\n\nThe G4 nations advocate for reforms of the Security Council to better represent contemporary geopolitical realities, reflecting the growing influence and contributions of these countries in global affairs. They propose an enlargement of the Security Council to include more permanent members beyond the current five (China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom, and the United States).",
